<figureCitation box="[151,264,1437,1463]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1–3" captionStart-1="FIGURES 4–7" captionStart-2="FIGURES 8–16" captionStartId-0="3.[151,264,1546,1570]" captionStartId-1="4.[151,264,1801,1825]" captionStartId-2="5.[151,264,1380,1404]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,315,1519]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1433,633,1778]" captionTargetBox-2="[151,1436,181,1357]" captionTargetId-0="figure-74@3.[151,1436,306,1519]" captionTargetId-1="figure-194@4.[151,1436,633,1778]" captionTargetId-2="figure-19@5.[151,1436,181,1357]" captionTargetPageId-0="3" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionTargetPageId-2="5" captionText-0="FIGURES 1–3. Borniella parva gen. &amp; spec. nov. holotype male from Sarawak, left male palp (1 prolateral, 2 ventral, 3 retrolateral). C—conductor, dTA— distal tegular apophysis, E—embolus, mTA—median tegular apophysis, pTA—proximal tegular apophysis, RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis, S—spermophor, ST—subtegulum." captionText-1="FIGURES 4–7. Borniella parva gen. &amp; spec. nov., female paratype from Sarawak. 4, 6 Epigyne, ventral; 5 Vulva, dorsal (internal duct system and rim of copulatory opening in red, epigynal pocket and parts of the inner rims in green); 7 Schematic course of internal duct system, ventral. CO—copulatory opening, CP—copulatory plug, EF—epigynal field, EP—epigynal pocket, FD—fertilization duct, GA—glandular appendages, LS—lobal septum, MSu—membranous sac (unexpanded), SP— spermatheca." captionText-2="FIGURES 8–16. Borniella parva gen. &amp; spec. nov., holotype male (8, 10, 13, 15) and female paratype (9, 11–12, 14, 16) from Sarawak. 8–9 Eyes, dorsal. 10–12 Claws (10 right leg II, prolateral claw, prolateral; 11 right palp, prolateral; 12 right leg II, retrolateral claw, retrolateral). 13–14 Left chelicera, ventral. 15–16 Trilobate membrane, distal metatarsus, dorsal (15 right leg III, 16 right leg I). LP—lateral projections, MH—median hook." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911153" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911159" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911161" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6911153/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6911159/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6911161/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figs 1–16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[276,349,1437,1464]" captionStart="FIGURES 82–97" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,182,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-19@19.[151,1436,181,1875]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 82–97. Heteropodinae gen. &amp; spp. nov., habitus (dorsal and ventral, respectively). 82–85 Borniella parva gen. &amp; spec. nov.; 86–89 Menarik kecil gen. &amp; spec. nov.; 90–93 Micropoda davisae gen. &amp; spec. nov.; 94–97 Tiomaniella ladam gen. &amp; spec. nov. (82–83, 86–87, 90–91, 94–95 holotype male, 84–85, 88–89, 92–93, 96–97 female paratype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911203/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">82–85</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[360,388,1437,1463]" captionStart="FIGURE 98" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1436,1460]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,956,1413]" captionTargetId="figure-372@20.[151,1436,956,1413]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 98. Distribution of the new genera and species in Malaysia, Brunei and Papua New Guinea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911205" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911205/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">98</figureCitation>
